.SH NAME
evolve-completion-zsh - Generate the autocompletion script for zsh


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBevolve completion zsh [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate the autocompletion script for the zsh shell.

.PP
If shell completion is not already enabled in your environment you will need
to enable it.  You can execute the following once:

.EX
echo "autoload -U compinit; compinit" >> ~/.zshrc
.EE

.PP
To load completions in your current shell session:

.EX
source <(evolve completion zsh)
.EE

.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:

.SS Linux:
.EX
evolve completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_evolve"
.EE

.SS macOS:
.EX
evolve completion zsh > $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh/site-functions/_evolve
.EE

.PP
You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for zsh

.PP
\fB--no-descriptions\fP[=false]
	disable completion descriptions


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	emit machine-readable JSONL progress on stdout

.PP
\fB--layout\fP="auto"
	repository layout: auto, marketplace, multi, or single

.PP
\fB--results-format\fP=""
	format for results files and the EVALUATION rollup: json, jsonc, or yaml (default: config results_format or json)

.PP
\fB--root\fP=""
	repository root to operate on (default: walk up from the current directory)

.PP
\fB--telemetry-dir\fP=""
	write OpenTelemetry traces/metrics/logs as JSON to this directory (default: off; overrides OTEL_* env vars)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable debug logging


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBevolve-completion(1)\fP
